    "Body": " Position Summary The Director of Stablecoin and Payments Ecosystems will be the go-to-expert, leading the day-to-day management of all aspects of the company's stablecoin project, including project planning and roadmap execution. This position drives and fosters relationships with the technology and compliance departments, government agencies, regulators, cryptocurrency ecosystem retail and banking participants, and other external partners forming the ecosystem for a successful global stablecoin market. One of the key aspects of the role includes building and mapping new product capabilities to capture flows via new infrastructures and business models. Essential Duties And Responsibilities The essential functions include, but are not limited to, the following: Develop and define the strategy and execution of the roadmap for the company's stablecoin project throughout the stablecoin product's lifecycle; define and execute strategic objectives in context of evolving business landscape Gather and prioritize customer requirements and use those requirements to continually define the stablecoin vision Write specifications and assist the technology team in building a stablecoin platform that customers will use, and external stakeholders will build on top of Manage relationships with key partners, including banks, exchanges, and cryptocurrency market participants Coordinate with internal development teams on a competitive and forward-thinking go-to-market strategy for our stablecoin and payments product offering Recommend and lead the launch of additional strategic products to precede market trends and optimize payments revenue and growth Work closely with the compliance department to research and apprise executive leadership of any compliance or regulatory hurdles Monitor the digital payment ecosystem and revise planning to ensure the product's features and specifications are superior to competing products and services, including analyzing potential partner relationships for both stablecoin and payments processing product offerings Partner with VP of Strategy and Engineering to lead stablecoin and payments product launches. In the near-term, lead our product design of stablecoin with the ultimate goal of adding integrated high-volume payments processing. Minimum Qualifications (knowledge, Skills, And Abilities) Strong understanding, interest, and relationships in payments instruments, payments processing, and decentralized finance Ability to translate critical information effectively across organization stakeholders including compliance, legal, technology, and marketing teams and executives Unique analytical, computer, and math skills with a proven ability to understand how new laws, regulations, policies, political environments, and economic trends impact financial services Demonstrated excellence in making informed judgments and setting priorities in constantly evolving startup environments Ability to collaborate with teammates and navigate relationships at the intersection of financial services and blockchain ecosystems Strong verbal and written communication skills Education/Experience Bachelor's degree, preferably in software engineering or finance Minimum of 6 years' experience in the finance industry Minimum of 2 years' experience in the crypto-asset industry preferred Experience with emerging e-commerce ventures, ideally from a payment processing perspective or related field Knowledge of regulatory and compliance issues preferred Blockchains Management, Inc. (\"Blockchains\") is proud to be a diverse workforce and we are committed to inclusion and diversity to ensure equal opportunity for all applicants. Blockchains provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants regardless of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, national origin, age marital status, physical or mental disability, veteran status or any other characteristic protected by federal,